             was indicted for <rs id="t18270405-249-off1367" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-off1367" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-off1367" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18270405-249-cd1368" type="crimeDate">20th of February</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-249-off1367 t18270405-249-cd1368"></join>, 1 great coat, value 4l.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18270405-249-victim1398" type="victimName">
                  Thomas 
                  Stephens
               <interp inst="t18270405-249-victim1398" type="surname" value="Stephens"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-victim1398" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-victim1398" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-249-off1367 t18270405-249-victim1398"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>THOMAS STEPHENS. I am a <rs id="t18270405-249-viclabel1369" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-249-victim1398 t18270405-249-viclabel1369"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18270405-249-crimeloc1370">London-wall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-249-crimeloc1370" type="placeName" value="London-wall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-249-crimeloc1370" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-249-off1367 t18270405-249-crimeloc1370"></join>. On the 20th of February, at three o'clock, when I went out, this coat was safe on my shop-board - the prisoner had come to enquire for work three or four days before; I put him to work, but as he could not do it, discharged him; I came home about five o'clock, but did not miss the coat till about three next day.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-249-person1399">
                  DANIEL 
                  STEPHENS
               <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1399" type="surname" value="STEPHENS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1399" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1399" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutor's brother. I was out at the time, but next day the boy who was in the care of the shop, said nobody but the prisoner had been there - I went and found him, and brought him to the shop; he denied the charge, but when I sent for an officer, he cried, and gave me the duplicate.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-249-person1400">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CREE
               <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1400" type="surname" value="CREE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1400" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1400" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. The prisoner pawned this coat on the evening of the 20th of February.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-249-person1401">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COOPER
               <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1401" type="surname" value="COOPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1401" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1401" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Stephens' shop, and went up stairs, leaving the prisoner there, and the coat on the board - he was gone when I returned, but I did not look for the coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-249-person1402">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1402" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1402" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-person1402" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took him in charge - he said he was in great distress.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a long written defence, stating that he could not obtain his wages from the prosecutor, which led him to commit the offence, in order to pay his lodgings.</p>
               <p>T. STEPHENS. I gave him a job - he spoiled it. I told him I would give him his victuals, but could pay him nothing - I never agreed to give him any wages - I gave him 2s. the night before this; I had not discharged him; I gave him 6s. and 1s. 6d.; he was with me three weeks and five days.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270405-249-verdict1371" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270405-249-verdict1371" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 23.</p>
